## Multi-Agent Orchestration

This project uses the [Agent Orchestrator](https://github.com/zanijr/claudesubagents) framework for routing tasks to specialized AI agents.

### How to Use

**Skills activate automatically** - just describe what you want:

| Say this... | What happens |
|------------|--------------|
| "List available agents" | Shows all agents from `.claude/agents/project/` |
| "Route this task to an agent" | Matches and dispatches via Task tool |
| "Create a new agent for X" | Walks through agent creation |
| "What agents can handle X?" | Finds matching agents |

### Adding Agents

Create `.md` files in `.claude/agents/project/` with YAML frontmatter defining `name`, `capabilities`, `triggers`, and `model`. Use the template at `.claude/agents/project/_template.md`.

### Configuration

See `orchestrator.config.json` for:
- `agentPaths` - Where agent files live
- `maxRetries` - Retry attempts with different agents (default: 2)
- `defaultModel` - Fallback model (default: sonnet)
